    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 27-SI SERIES, TYPE 200 - REPAIR PROCEDURES - RECTIFIER BRIDGE CHECK</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="1">
        <title>RECTIFIER BRIDGE CHECK</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>(Omit for Overcharged Battery)</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The rectifier bridge has a grounded heat sink and an insulated heat sink (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0801510">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0801510" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801510" filename="../figg08/G0801510.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Rectifier Bridge Check</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. DISCONNECT LEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>B. CONNECT OHMMETER TO FLAT METAL CLIP AND NOT THREADED STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. INSULATED HEAT SINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. INSULATED SCREWS (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. INSULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. END FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. SPRING WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. GROUND SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. GROUNDED HEAT SINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. OHMMETER</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. GROUND SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>To check the rectifier bridge:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the ohmmeter lead to a heat sink and another lead to the flat metal clips (not
                    to threaded stud). Press down firmly on metal clip.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reverse lead directions. If both readings are the same, replace the rectifier bridge.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat this same test between the same heat sink and the other two metal clips, between
                    the other heat sink and the three metal clips.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
